    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "service, endings.\nTWO: YOUR PERSONAL NUMBERS AND PERSONAL YEARS.\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1569600,
    "dDurationMs": 2560,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "YOU ARE ENDOWED at birth \nwith your own four personal\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1572160,
    "dDurationMs": 3520,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "numbers. These numbers tell you \nthe lessons to be learned during\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1575680,
    "dDurationMs": 4280,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "your life and the spiritual growth \nand development which you can attain.\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1579960,
    "dDurationMs": 5520,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "The 4 personal numbers are: the Life \nLesson Number, the Soul Number,\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1585480,
    "dDurationMs": 4360,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "the Outer Personality Number \nand the Path of Destiny Number.\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1589840,
    "dDurationMs": 3520,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "Your personal numbers are determined \nby the numbers in your birthdate\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1593360,
    "dDurationMs": 4680,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "and the letters in the name you are given \nat birth. To arrive at the numerical\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1598040,
    "dDurationMs": 5200,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "vibration of names, each letter in the \nalphabet is given a number value. A is\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1603240,
    "dDurationMs": 6640,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "1; B is 2; C is 3; and so on to Z, which is 26.\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1609880,
    "dDurationMs": 4400,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "To work with the value of the letters \nbeyond I, which is number 9, we\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1614280,
    "dDurationMs": 5600,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "reduce the value to a single digit. \nFor example, L is number 12. \n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1619880,
    "dDurationMs": 3200,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "We reduce the 12 by adding the \nfirst digit to the second; \n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1623080,
    "dDurationMs": 8480,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "or 1 + 2 equals 3. The number 12 is\nthen written as 12/3. The letter T is 20.\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1631560,
    "dDurationMs": 3160,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "We reduce the 20 by adding the \nfirst digit to the second, \n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1634720,
    "dDurationMs": 6520,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "or 2 + 0 equals 2. The number \n20 is then written as 20/2.\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1641240,
    "dDurationMs": 4080,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "The table below gives the number \nvalue of each letter in the alphabet.\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1645320,
    "dDurationMs": 3800,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "Learn this code thoroughly. Then you \nwon’t have to keep referring to the\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1649120,
    "dDurationMs": 4640,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "table, which can be a slow and tedious \nprocess. The more you work with the\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1653760,
    "dDurationMs": 4080,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "code, the easier it will come to you.\nNotice that there are patterns you can  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1657840,
    "dDurationMs": 8360,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "learn. For example: A; J; and S, all\nreduce to 1. B; K; and T, reduce to 2. C;  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1666200,
    "dDurationMs": 5800,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "L; and U, reduce to 3... and so on.\nTrain yourself by saying over and over: \n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1672000,
    "dDurationMs": 4680,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "AJS. AJS. AJS.\nBKT. BKT. BKT.\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1676680,
    "dDurationMs": 4480,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "There are memory tricks you can \nuse. For instance: number 6 is FOX.\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1681160,
    "dDurationMs": 4440,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "That’s an easy one. GPY sounds \nsomething like gypsy for number 7 - and\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1685600,
    "dDurationMs": 4600,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "number 8, HQZ, might remind you \nof headquarters. Use your own\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1690200,
    "dDurationMs": 3560,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "memory pegs so that the code will be \nreadily accessible when working out\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1693760,
    "dDurationMs": 3720,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "the value of words.\nWe can reduce any word to a number  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1697480,
    "dDurationMs": 4560,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "vibration by using our table, so let’s\nexperiment with a few words before we  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1702040,
    "dDurationMs": 4400,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "begin with names. Place the\nnumber value above each letter,  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1706440,
    "dDurationMs": 4720,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "add the values, and reduce the total to a\nsingle digit, if necessary.\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1711160,
    "dDurationMs": 4400,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "There are 4 double digits which are \nnot generally reduced. These are\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1715560,
    "dDurationMs": 4040,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "called the master numbers. Master \nnumbers offer more opportunity for\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1719600,
    "dDurationMs": 3880,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "expression and thus demand more effort \nfrom the individual or thing in\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1723480,
    "dDurationMs": 7120,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "question. The master numbers are 11, \n22, 33, and 44. Whenever you arrive\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1730600,
    "dDurationMs": 3600,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "at one of these numbers, retain \nthe master number value.\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1734200,
    "dDurationMs": 7440,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "For instance: take the word \"LIGHT\". \n3 + 9 + 7 + 8 + 2 equals 29, \n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1741640,
    "dDurationMs": 4000,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "and 2 + 9 equals 11.\nBecause “light” vibrates to  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1745640,
    "dDurationMs": 7720,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "master number 11, it is written as 29/11 rather\nthan 29/2, which would be the case if we reduced  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1753360,
    "dDurationMs": 4520,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "it entirely. However, 2 is\nstill acknowledged as the  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1757880,
    "dDurationMs": 6320,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "base number, and the word in question will\nfluctuate between the vibrations of 2 and 11.\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1764200,
    "dDurationMs": 3960,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "An individual will fluctuate between \nany master number and its base\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1768160,
    "dDurationMs": 4120,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "digit because the vibration of the \nmaster number is so intense and so\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1772280,
    "dDurationMs": 5600,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "powerful that it cannot be lived under \ncontinuously. Therefore, living under\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1777880,
    "dDurationMs": 4560,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "the base number for a brief period \noffers a moment of respite where one\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1782440,
    "dDurationMs": 3560,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "gathers one’s forces before attempting \nto work with the master number\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1786000,
    "dDurationMs": 4200,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "vibration again. Master numbers \ndemand the greatest output from the\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1790200,
    "dDurationMs": 4480,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "individual, and, in return, \noffer the greatest reward.\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1794680,
    "dDurationMs": 4320,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "A name that vibrates to a master number is: \nMELANIE MAE CLARKE;\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1799000,
    "dDurationMs": 3960,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "which equals 65/11. \nAgain, this number would  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1802960,
    "dDurationMs": 6040,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "not be reduced further, because it is a master\nnumber. However, this individual will fluctuate  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1809000,
    "dDurationMs": 3720,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "between her master number\n11 and the base number 2. The  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1812720,
    "dDurationMs": 6960,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "word “roses” vibrates to 22: \n9 + 6 + 1 + 5 + 1 equals 22.\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1819680,
    "dDurationMs": 3800,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "We do not reduce the 22 \nbecause it is a master number.\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1823480,
    "dDurationMs": 4920,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "In this system of numerology, we \nonly use the numbers 1 to 78, for\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1828400,
    "dDurationMs": 4400,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "reasons which we explained in the \nintroduction. When totaling a name, if\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1832800,
    "dDurationMs": 4160,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "you arrive at a number above 78, \nsimply reduce that number to the next\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1836960,
    "dDurationMs": 4840,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "lower double digit or single digit, \nas the case may be. For example, if a\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1841800,
    "dDurationMs": 6880,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "personal number totals 86, add the 8 + \n6, and work with the 14/5 vibration.\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1848680,
    "dDurationMs": 5600,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "Or if the personal number totals 106, \nadd the 1 + 0 + 6, and work with the 7\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1854280,
    "dDurationMs": 3360,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "vibration.\nRemember, all double digits  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1857640,
    "dDurationMs": 5320,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "that reduce to the same base number have\nthe same basic meaning. The double digit  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1862960,
    "dDurationMs": 4200,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "reflects a variation of the single\nnumber. You could liken this to living  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1867160,
    "dDurationMs": 4480,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "in the same city but on different\nstreets. Therefore, the numbers 12,  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1871640,
    "dDurationMs": 8520,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "21, 30, 39, 48, 57, 66 and 75 \nall reflect the basic 3; however,  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1880160,
    "dDurationMs": 3840,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "the double digit expresses a variation\nof the original 3.\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1884000,
    "dDurationMs": 3240,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "Now that you know how to reduce any \nword, we will demonstrate how to\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1887240,
    "dDurationMs": 5360,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "arrive at your four personal numbers \nand explain what those numbers mean.\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1892600,
    "dDurationMs": 3640,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "The Life Lesson Number.\nThe 1st of the 4 personal  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1896240,
    "dDurationMs": 4800,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "numbers we will discuss is called the Life\nLesson Number. It represents the lessons you  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1901040,
    "dDurationMs": 3200,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "must learn in this lifetime and\nis most significant in your  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1904240,
    "dDurationMs": 4920,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "choice of a career. It is\nderived from your full birthdate. Even  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1909160,
    "dDurationMs": 3120,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "a business or idea has a moment of\nbirth, and can therefore be  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1912280,
    "dDurationMs": 3960,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "treated in the same way.\nWe will use as an example,  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1916240,
    "dDurationMs": 7240,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "Ada Wynn Lunt, born November 12, 1940.\n1st, reduce the birthdate to numbers.  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1923480,
    "dDurationMs": 4280,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "November is the 11th month;\ntherefore, Ada’s birthdate is written:  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1927760,
    "dDurationMs": 6160,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "11 dash 12 dash 1940. Remember to write the\nfull year of birth; not an abbreviated  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1933920,
    "dDurationMs": 4400,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "form such as 40. Next, reduce the\nyear to a double digit by adding the  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1938320,
    "dDurationMs": 8040,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "year through once: 1 + 9 + 4 + 0 equals 14.\nNow we total the birthdate once more:\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1946360,
    "dDurationMs": 10240,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "11 + 12 + 1940 equals 11 + 12 + \n14. 11 + 12 + 14 equals 37/1.\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1956600,
    "dDurationMs": 6200,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "37 is reduced by adding the 1st digit \nto the 2nd, or 3 + 7 which equals 10.\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1962800,
    "dDurationMs": 4880,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "Reduce the 10 in the same manner \nby adding 1 + 0. 37 is then\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1967680,
    "dDurationMs": 5200,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "written as 37/1. This is \nAda’s Life Lesson Number.\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1972880,
    "dDurationMs": 2960,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "The Life Lesson Number is a \nconstant and cannot be changed or\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1975840,
    "dDurationMs": 4320,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "modified in any way because it is \nderived from the birthdate. It indicates\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1980160,
    "dDurationMs": 4960,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "vocation plus the lesson you came into \nincarnation to overcome or to learn.\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1985120,
    "dDurationMs": 3680,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "It also represents the cosmic gift you \nare given in order to accomplish your\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1988800,
    "dDurationMs": 2320,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "destiny.\nFind your Life Lesson  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1991120,
    "dDurationMs": 5120,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "Number by following the same procedure. Then\nread the delineation of the Life Lesson  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1996240,
    "dDurationMs": 4960,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "Number single digit below. For a\nfiner delineation of the double digit,  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 2001200,
    "dDurationMs": 4760,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "go to Part 2 of this book.\nIn our example, Ada has a 37 or  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 2005960,
    "dDurationMs": 4480,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "1 Life Lesson Number. She would read\nnumber 1 under the Life Lesson Number  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 2010440,
    "dDurationMs": 4880,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "section following. She would then\nturn to Part 2 page 120 for the  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 2015320,
    "dDurationMs": 6200,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "delineation of the 37 - a more explicit\ndescription of the basic number 1.\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 2021520,
    "dDurationMs": 3920,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "1 AS THE LIFE LESSON: You \nmust learn to be original,\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 2025440,
    "dDurationMs": 3360,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "strong-willed, creative and innovative. \nYou should have the courage\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 2028800,
    "dDurationMs": 4400,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "and drive to go ahead into new fields \nof expression and be a pioneer. You\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 2033200,
    "dDurationMs": 5320,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "should always go forward, never turn \nback. At times you may be dictatorial\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 2038520,
    "dDurationMs": 4440,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "and stubborn because you do not like to \nbe restricted or directed. You are a\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 2042960,
    "dDurationMs": 6400,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "good executive, and work best alone. You \nare usually efficient and well-organized. \n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 2049360,
    "dDurationMs": 2920,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "You are not naturally domestic \nbut can manage well in any\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 2052280,
    "dDurationMs": 4600,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "situation. You usually like sports and \nathletics, and enjoy the thrill of\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 2056880,
    "dDurationMs": 4600,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "winning. You are sophisticated, not \nemotionally romantic, and always\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 2061480,
    "dDurationMs": 4040,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "appear at the head of social and \ncommercial groups. By learning the lessons\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 2065520,
    "dDurationMs": 4760,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "of number 1, you become intimately \nfamiliar with the God energy, that\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 2070280,
    "dDurationMs": 5680,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "probing, seeking, independent spark \nthat moves all creation. You are\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 2075960,
    "dDurationMs": 3560,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "creative on the physical plane because \nyour pioneer spirit precedes all\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 2079520,
    "dDurationMs": 6920,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "others, and expresses your unique individuality.\n2 AS THE LIFE LESSON: You are here to  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 2086440,
    "dDurationMs": 2440,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "learn to become a\ngood mixer. You are a  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 2088880,
    "dDurationMs": 4360,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "good salesperson, more persuasive than\nforceful. You should be a support for  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 2093240,
    "dDurationMs": 4640,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "those in the leadership role, help them\nto find their goals in life, and remain  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 2097880,
    "dDurationMs": 4240,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "behind the scenes if necessary. This\nquality can be a help to you in  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 2102120,
    "dDurationMs": 4720,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "business because those who benefit from\nyour talents will in turn help you make use  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 2106840,
    "dDurationMs": 4760,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "of your abilities. In partnerships\nand groups, you will encounter the  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 2111600,
    "dDurationMs": 6080,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "lessons you came to learn in this\nlifetime. Success is then very possible.  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 2117680,
    "dDurationMs": 3280,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "You must have consideration for\nothers, and should bring people  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 2120960,
    "dDurationMs": 4800,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "together for a common cause. Various\nprofessions are open to you as you learn  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 2125760,
    "dDurationMs": 3880,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "to be adaptable to most things that\nneed to be done. You could select  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 2129640,
    "dDurationMs": 7920,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "a career in finance, music, medicine,\nreligion or statistical analysis and research.\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 2137560,
    "dDurationMs": 3880,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "3 AS THE LIFE LESSON: You \nare best in intellectual,\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 2141440,
    "dDurationMs": 4960,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "artistic or creative endeavors. You \nneed to express, to manifest and to\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 2146400,
    "dDurationMs": 4720,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "see the results of your work. Beauty, \nfruitfulness, luxury and pleasure are\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 2151120,
    "dDurationMs": 4120,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "your keywords. You should have \nambition and pride. You must become\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 2155240,
    "dDurationMs": 3560,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "conscious of the law, and, by being \nan excellent disciplinarian, you will\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 2158800,
    "dDurationMs": 4920,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "achieve a position of authority over \nothers. 3 combines the daring of 1 with\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 2163720,
    "dDurationMs": 4520,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "the caution of 2. It is a number of \nself-expression and freedom and is\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 2168240,
