      "utf8": "E AS THE FIRST VOWEL: You have \nan eventful, exciting life. \n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5293200,
    "dDurationMs": 3360,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "You are versatile and have the \nability to learn easily, but\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5296560,
    "dDurationMs": 4520,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "may be nervous and temperamental. If \nE is the first vowel and there are\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5301080,
    "dDurationMs": 3040,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "more than 3 E’s in the name, \nyou may have a fickle nature.\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5305600,
    "dDurationMs": 3400,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "I AS THE FIRST VOWEL: You are intuitive and\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5309000,
    "dDurationMs": 5040,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "interested in the arts, drama and/or \nscience. If I is the first vowel and\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5314040,
    "dDurationMs": 4640,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "there are more than 3 I’s in the \nname, you are sensitive, shy and too\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5318680,
    "dDurationMs": 2920,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "emotional.\nO AS THE FIRST VOWEL  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5321600,
    "dDurationMs": 4640,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "in the first name: You are frank,\nmethodical and believe in law,  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5326240,
    "dDurationMs": 5600,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "system and order. If O is the first\nvowel and there are more than 3 O’s in the name,  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5331840,
    "dDurationMs": 3920,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "you can be obstinate,\nslow and monotonous.\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5335760,
    "dDurationMs": 4280,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "U AS THE FIRST VOWEL in the \nfirst name: You have a universal\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5340040,
    "dDurationMs": 4040,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "mind capable of great ideas and \na broad viewpoint. You love to\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5344080,
    "dDurationMs": 4800,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "accumulate material things. \nSymbolically, the U is a cup that holds,\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5348880,
    "dDurationMs": 4360,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "therefore you may become a collector. \nIf U is the first vowel and there are\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5353240,
    "dDurationMs": 4080,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "more than 3 U’s you may experience \nloss and selfishness because the\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5357320,
    "dDurationMs": 5760,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "cup spills over and the contents are \nlost. When W is the first vowel in the\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5363080,
    "dDurationMs": 7840,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "first name, it vibrates like a double U.\nY AS THE FIRST VOWEL in the first name:  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5370920,
    "dDurationMs": 2800,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "It has the same\nsignificance as E or I,  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5373720,
    "dDurationMs": 4920,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "according to the sound produced. To\ndetermine when Y is used as a vowel,  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5378640,
    "dDurationMs": 5920,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "consider the pronunciation. In the\nname May or Wayne, Y is not a vowel  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5384560,
    "dDurationMs": 4440,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "but if Y has a separate sound, as in\nthe name Floyd, it is counted as a  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5389000,
    "dDurationMs": 5040,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "double vowel diphthong since the sound of\nthe Y is distinguishable in the pronunciation.  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5395400,
    "dDurationMs": 3120,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "In a name such as Lynn or\nWynn, where the Y is the only  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5398520,
    "dDurationMs": 6600,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "vowel sound, it is counted as a vowel. In the\nnames Yvonne or Yvette, Y as the first vowel  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5405120,
    "dDurationMs": 5400,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "has the sound of E. Also, in a\nname such as Mary or Harry,  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5410520,
    "dDurationMs": 5240,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "Y is a vowel because it sounds like E.\nOne last note on the vowel or consonant  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5415760,
    "dDurationMs": 4280,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "Y. Its two-pronged structure\ncould symbolically indicate its double  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5420040,
    "dDurationMs": 4760,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "usage in the alphabet. As a vowel\nsound, Y could become the  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5424800,
    "dDurationMs": 5520,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "27th letter in the alphabet to\ncomplete the 9th vibration presently missing.\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5430320,
    "dDurationMs": 8720,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "(I equals 9; R equals 18 or 9; Y equals 27 or 9).\nPythagoras considered Y such a high mystical  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5439040,
    "dDurationMs": 3000,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "letter that at one time he took\nthe name of Yarancharya to  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5442040,
    "dDurationMs": 5040,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "experience its vibration first hand.\nIf the name contains 2 vowels together,  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5447080,
    "dDurationMs": 5560,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "as in the name Faith, then read\nthe qualities of both vowels. For  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5452640,
    "dDurationMs": 5360,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "example, Faith indicates a person who is\nindependent, interested in research (A),  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5458000,
    "dDurationMs": 5200,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "and also very intuitive, a lover of\nmusic and the arts (I).\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5463200,
    "dDurationMs": 2720,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "We do not count the vowels in \nthe name beyond the 1st vowel\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5465920,
    "dDurationMs": 4920,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "combination unless there are identical \nadjoining vowels later in the name.\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5470840,
    "dDurationMs": 5400,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "In the name \"Faith May Winter\", we \nconsider AI as the first vowel. Because\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5476240,
    "dDurationMs": 5040,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "the AI combination appears nowhere else \nin the name, the first AI stands as\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5481280,
    "dDurationMs": 4880,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "the only one of that vowel. The A in \nMay and the I in Winter are considered\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5486160,
    "dDurationMs": 4720,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "separately. Conversely, should the \nname be Faith Daisy Waite, we would\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5490880,
    "dDurationMs": 4800,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "have 3 AI vowels to consider. The \nfollowing is a list of diphthongs and\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5495680,
    "dDurationMs": 4280,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "double vowels in sample names.\nTriple vowels, such as in the name  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5499960,
    "dDurationMs": 4000,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "Louise, would also combine the\nqualities of the 3 vowels.\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5503960,
    "dDurationMs": 3480,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "Other meanings of the vowels will be \nfound in the list of the ABC’s in\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5507440,
    "dDurationMs": 3680,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "Chapter 5, which gives the meanings \nof the individual letters of the\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5511120,
    "dDurationMs": 4280,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "alphabet.\nYour Personal Year.\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5515400,
    "dDurationMs": 4440,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "We live our lives in 9 year cycles, \nincorporating the universal principles\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5519840,
    "dDurationMs": 5280,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "of the numbers 1 thru 9. When we \nfinish the 9th cycle, we begin again\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5525120,
    "dDurationMs": 5120,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "with 1 and proceed again through the \n9 numbers. This cycle occurs over\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5530240,
    "dDurationMs": 4840,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "and over throughout our lifetime. \nLook back 9 years from this moment,\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5535080,
    "dDurationMs": 3520,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "and you will find that you are \nexperiencing not the exact events but a\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5538600,
    "dDurationMs": 4840,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "similar type vibration. For instance, \n9 years ago you might have been\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5543440,
    "dDurationMs": 4400,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "saving money to build a home; now \nyou may be saving to send a child to\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5547840,
    "dDurationMs": 5480,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "college. The event is different, but \nthe underlying theme is the same:\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5553320,
    "dDurationMs": 5480,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "budgeting money. If you know what to \nexpect in any given cycle, you can\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5558800,
    "dDurationMs": 4360,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "live in tune with your particular \nvibration, and make your life easier,\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5563160,
    "dDurationMs": 4760,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "happier and more productive.\nTo find your present personal year,  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5567920,
    "dDurationMs": 3280,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "simply add the month and day of\nyour birth to the year of your last  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5571200,
    "dDurationMs": 5440,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "birthday. For example: November 12,\n1940 is the birthdate of Ada Wynn  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5576640,
    "dDurationMs": 4840,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "Lunt. To determine Ada’s present\nvibration, we will add the date.  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5581480,
    "dDurationMs": 10160,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "11 + 12 + 1975. (1975 was the year of her last\nbirthday as of this book's writing.) Remember,  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5591640,
    "dDurationMs": 3240,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "we do not use the year of\nbirth, but rather the year of  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5594880,
    "dDurationMs": 6800,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "the last birthday. If you were born on February\n29, use February 29 regardless of whether the  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5601680,
    "dDurationMs": 4160,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "year in question had a\nFebruary 29th or not.\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5605840,
    "dDurationMs": 6240,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "Ada, in 1975, is in a 45 or 9 personal \nyear. The personal year runs from the\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5612080,
    "dDurationMs": 4320,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "birthday of one year to the birthday \nof the next year, not from January to\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5616400,
    "dDurationMs": 5720,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "December as the general calendar runs. \nTherefore, Ada will be in a 45 or 9\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5622120,
    "dDurationMs": 7040,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "personal year from November 12, 1975 \nto November 12, 1976, even though\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5629160,
    "dDurationMs": 7160,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "most of her personal year, 1975, \nruns into the calendar year 1976.\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5636320,
    "dDurationMs": 3920,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "Ada would then turn to Part 2 and \nread number 9 under the section\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5640240,
    "dDurationMs": 5640,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "entitled 9 as a Temporary Vibration. \nShe would then read 45 or 9 as a\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5645880,
    "dDurationMs": 3960,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "Temporary Vibration, which is a finer \ndescription of the underlying 9\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5649840,
    "dDurationMs": 4360,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "Temporary Vibration. Note that we are \nnot reading the number as a Personal\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5654200,
    "dDurationMs": 4280,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "Vibration. The numerical meanings of \na Personal Number and a Temporary\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5658480,
    "dDurationMs": 3840,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "Vibration are the same; however, \nyou must put them in their proper\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5662320,
    "dDurationMs": 4320,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "perspectives. If a number is your \nPersonal Number, it is with you for a\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5666640,
    "dDurationMs": 6640,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "lifetime. If it is a Temporary Vibration, \nyou experience it for a short time.\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5673280,
    "dDurationMs": 6040,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "So, from her November 12, 1975 \nbirthday to her November 12, 1976\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5679320,
    "dDurationMs": 5960,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "birthday Ada will be temporarily \nexperiencing a 45 or 9 vibration.\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5685280,
    "dDurationMs": 3360,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "You can follow the same procedure for \nany given year of your life to find\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5688640,
    "dDurationMs": 4280,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "out what happened or what is going to \nhappen. Merely choose the time you\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5692920,
    "dDurationMs": 6680,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "are investigating, for instance, the \nsummer of 1946, or the fall of 1987, and\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5699600,
    "dDurationMs": 4920,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "from there determine the year of your \nlast birthday at that time. Then add\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5704520,
    "dDurationMs": 3320,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "that year to your month and day of \nbirth to find your personal year\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5707840,
    "dDurationMs": 4000,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "vibration.\nPeriod Numbers.\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5711840,
    "dDurationMs": 4040,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "We can divide the personal year into \n3 equal blocks of time to determine\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5715880,
    "dDurationMs": 4120,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "what is happening in each 4 month \nperiod of the year. We do this in the\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5720000,
    "dDurationMs": 3800,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "following manner.\nPlace the personal year calculations in the  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5723800,
    "dDurationMs": 3760,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "first column. At the head of the\n2nd column write the month of the  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5727560,
    "dDurationMs": 4240,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "birthday and the 4th month\nfollowing; in our example,  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5731800,
    "dDurationMs": 6920,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "November to March. In the next column, place\nthe following 4 months: March to July,  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5738720,
    "dDurationMs": 5840,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "and in the last column place\nthe remaining 4 months, July to November.\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5744560,
    "dDurationMs": 3840,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "If the birth month were June, you \nwould place June to October at the\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5748400,
    "dDurationMs": 4440,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "head of the 2nd column, October \nto February in the 3rd column and\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5752840,
    "dDurationMs": 4760,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "February to June in the 4th column. \nThis simply divides the year into\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5757600,
    "dDurationMs": 4080,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "3 four-month blocks beginning \nwith the month of your birth.\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5761680,
    "dDurationMs": 5000,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "To find the experience of Ada’s 1st \nfour-month block in 1975, add her\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5766680,
    "dDurationMs": 7600,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "age to the year 1975. She was 35 \non November 12, 1975, so we will\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5774280,
    "dDurationMs": 5720,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "add 1975 and 35 to get 2010. We \nwill then reduce 2010 by adding \n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5780000,
    "dDurationMs": 5800,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "2 + 0 + 1 + 0 to get 3. She \nwill be under a 3 vibration \n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5785800,
    "dDurationMs": 6680,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "from November 1975 to March \n1976 of her personal year 45/9.\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5792480,
    "dDurationMs": 3800,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "In the 2nd block, covering March to \nJuly, we add the double digit of\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5796280,
    "dDurationMs": 9800,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "her Life Lesson Number 37 to the year \n1975. 1975 + 37 is 2012, or 2 + 0 +\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5806080,
    "dDurationMs": 7280,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "1 + 2 is 5. From March to July she \nwill be operating under a 5 vibration.\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5813360,
    "dDurationMs": 3800,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "In the. 4th column under July to \nNovember, we will add the double\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5817160,
    "dDurationMs": 7880,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "digit of her Soul Number to the year \n1975, or 1975 + 12 to get 1987. \n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5825040,
    "dDurationMs": 6640,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "1 + 9 + 8 + 7 is 25 or 7 vibration.\nAlways add the unreduced double  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5831680,
    "dDurationMs": 4200,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "digit of the Life Lesson Number to the\n3rd column and the unreduced double digit  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5835880,
    "dDurationMs": 2800,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "of the Soul Number to the\n4th column.\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5838680,
    "dDurationMs": 3320,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "The delineations for these numbers \nare in Part 2 of this book under the\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5842000,
    "dDurationMs": 3680,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "Temporary Vibrations section \nof each individual number.\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 5845680,
    "dDurationMs": 3960,
    "segs": [ {
