    "dDurationMs": 5160,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "End of Main Book.\nAPPENDIX. SYNTHESIS  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 39714199,
    "dDurationMs": 7359,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "OF NUMEROLOGY, ASTROLOGY AND THE TAROT.\nNUMEROLOGY, ASTROLOGY AND THE TAROT are different\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 39721559,
    "dDurationMs": 4602,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "ways of exploring the cycles of life \nexperience. In this Appendix, the\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 39726160,
    "dDurationMs": 3680,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "material presented in Part 2 of this \nbook is summarized in table and chart\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 39729840,
    "dDurationMs": 3398,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "form so that you can more easily \nsee how each of these three ancient\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 39733238,
    "dDurationMs": 4480,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "systems relates to the others.\nAs you know, the 78 keys of the  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 39737719,
    "dDurationMs": 4242,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "Tarot are divided into 2 groups: \nthe Major Arcana and the Minor  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 39741961,
    "dDurationMs": 4117,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "Arcana. The Major Arcana\ncorrespond to the numbers 0  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 39746078,
    "dDurationMs": 7039,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "to 22. These numbers are: the God-powered 0,\nthe base digits 1 to 9 and the first cycle of  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 39753117,
    "dDurationMs": 4523,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "double-digit numbers up to the\nsecond master number, 22. These  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 39757641,
    "dDurationMs": 4277,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "numbers and their corresponding Tarot\nkeys represent archetypal life patterns  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 39761918,
    "dDurationMs": 3840,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "and are linked astrologically with the\nsigns of the zodiac and the planets.  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 39766438,
    "dDurationMs": 5480,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "This information is contained in Table 1.\nIn Tables 2 to 5, we present the information  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 39771918,
    "dDurationMs": 3762,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "contained in Chapters 2 to 5\nof Part 2, which deal with the  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 39775680,
    "dDurationMs": 7199,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "numbers 23 to 78, the Minor Arcana and the\nyearly astrological cycle. To clarify the  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 39782879,
    "dDurationMs": 3762,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "relationship of these numbers to the\nMinor Arcana and the astrological cycle  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 39786641,
    "dDurationMs": 3199,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "we have included Figure 7, which\npresents the information of  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 39789840,
    "dDurationMs": 5398,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "Tables 2 to 5 in wheel form.\nIn astrology we speak of Aries (fire),  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 39795238,
    "dDurationMs": 5121,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "Cancer (water), Libra (air) and\nCapricorn (earth) as the cardinal  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 39800359,
    "dDurationMs": 4359,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "signs. The cardinal signs govern the\nseasons and mark the equinoxes and  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 39804719,
    "dDurationMs": 5602,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "solstices. For example, the astrological\nyear begins with the Vernal Equinox;  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 39810320,
    "dDurationMs": 5117,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "this occurs when the Sun enters the\nsign Aries, and marks the beginning of spring.\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 39815438,
    "dDurationMs": 4801,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "In Figure 7 you will see that the \nking, queen and page of each suit\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 39820238,
    "dDurationMs": 4121,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "correspond to the cardinal sign which \ngoverns the same element. The King\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 39824359,
    "dDurationMs": 5602,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "of Wands (cardinal, fire) corresponds \nto Aries (cardinal, fire).\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 39829961,
    "dDurationMs": 4316,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "You will also note in the tables and \nin Figure 7 that in the cardinal signs\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 39834277,
    "dDurationMs": 4160,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "the kings, queens and pages of each \nsuit are assigned the same astrological\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 39838438,
    "dDurationMs": 4641,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "correspondence as the twos, threes and \nfours of the same suit. For example,\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 39843078,
    "dDurationMs": 5320,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "in Table 3 and in Figure 7, the King \nof Cups (37 or 1) and the 2 of Cups\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 39848398,
    "dDurationMs": 6563,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "(42 or 6) both correspond to the 1st decan \nof Cancer (0 degrees to 10 degrees Cancer). \n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 39854961,
    "dDurationMs": 4316,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "Here, the King acts in a role of royal \nprotector ship, overshadowing the Two,\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 39859277,
    "dDurationMs": 4203,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "which is at an earlier point in the \ncycle. Each card represents different\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 39863480,
    "dDurationMs": 6480,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "manifestations of the same astrological energy.\nThere are two other important cards in each suit:  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 39869961,
    "dDurationMs": 4680,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "the knights and the aces.\nEach knight is pictured on horseback,  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 39874641,
    "dDurationMs": 4000,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "representing movement and energy,\nand because of this symbolism the  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 39878641,
    "dDurationMs": 5078,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "knights have come to represent entire\nseasons. Thus the Knight of Wands governs  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 39883719,
    "dDurationMs": 3480,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "the spring, carrying the initial\nburst of Aries energy through the  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 39887199,
    "dDurationMs": 4719,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "spring months of Aries, Taurus and\nGemini, until the Sun reaches 0 degrees  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 39891918,
    "dDurationMs": 4563,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "Cancer and the Knight of Cups begins his\njourney through the summer season.\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 39896480,
    "dDurationMs": 4078,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "Just as each knight rules an entire \nseason, each ace rules an entire\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 39900559,
    "dDurationMs": 4480,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "element. The power inherent in the ace \ncorresponds to all the manifestations\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 39905039,
    "dDurationMs": 4199,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "of an element. Thus, the Ace of Swords \ncorresponds to the entire element of\n "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 39909238,
    "dDurationMs": 6402,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "air and rules the air signs \nLibra, Aquarius and Gemini."
    } ]
  } ]
}
